## Testing plan

- `build` gate: `dotnet build Berreman.slnx -c Release` from `Berreman/` MUST pass with `CurvedElements.fs` compiling against the reused engine seams; no fork of `OpticalSystemSolver`/`EmFieldSystem`/`OpticalProperties`/`Constants.fs`.
- `unit-tests` gate: `dotnet test --no-build -c Release` from `Berreman/BerremanTests/` stays green (this slice does not touch `BerremanTests`).
- `constructor-unit-tests` gate (project `OpticalConstructor.Tests`, slice 001): MUST pass and increase the count over the prior baseline.
  - `CurvedElementsTests.fs` — AC-C1 (radius/aperture in nm/µm/mm stored as `double<meter>` matching `Constants.fs` factors, no non-SI value left); AC-C2 (`sampleZones surface n` returns n uniform zones, axis zone `localAoiShift = Angle.zero`); AC-C3 (`solveZone` feeds `incidenceAngle` shifted by `localAoiShift` via `IncidentLightInfo.rotateY` to `OpticalSystemSolver`, result carries the `Solution.emSys` split); AC-C5 (concave→negative / convex→positive radius, no override flag, `sag` signed height); AC-C6 (`gradeCoating` scales finite `Thickness.Thickness d`, leaves `Thickness.Infinity`, all `double<meter>`, ~5% default); AC-C7 (gap propagated by `EmField.propagate` over a `Layer` whose thickness is the axial separation, no second routine); AC-C8 (grading-disabled element shares one immutable `OpticalSystem` coating).
  - `BeamTreeTests.fs` (extended) — AC-C4: `attachCurvedElement` on `ConstructorElement.CurvedMirror` gives every zone `BeamNode` a `Reflected` child and no `Transmitted` child; on `ConstructorElement.Lens` every zone node exposes both branches.

## Risks

- **Medium.** The curved-element path is the single admitted physics extension; the load-bearing correctness is the local-AOI shift (`rotateY`) feeding the unforked `OpticalSystemSolver`, the signed-radius convention, and the per-zone grading rescale that must touch only finite `Thickness` cases. Mitigation: keep `CurvedElements.fs` confined to the Domain project; reuse the three named engine seams unchanged (no second propagator, no ABCD module, no second engine); prove the axis-zone equivalence to the flat solver, the sign convention, the finite-vs-`Infinity` grading, and the mirror-vs-lens branch shapes by unit test before exit; keep all fields in canonical SI so they serialize through the existing `constructorElement` `$def` with no FsPickler path.

## Hand-off

The curved-element domain exists in `CurvedElements.fs`: `CurvedSurface`/`SurfaceFigure`/`LocalZone`, the `sag`/`sampleZones`/`solveZone`/`attachCurvedElement`/`gradeCoating` functions, the signed-radius convention, coating reuse, and EUV depth-graded period scaling — all over the reused engine seams and the slice-002 `BeamTree`, unit-tested. Later slices (E sources, F results, G synthesis/fit, H optimizers, I persistence, J builders) build on the now-complete Parts A–D foundation. Emit the state-of-the-world file with all required ATX headings (`Where we are`, `What's working`, `Tests`, `Architecture`, `Deferred`, `Gotchas`, `Changelog`) and a fenced `gates:` YAML baseline block carrying the updated `constructor-unit-tests` count so the next slice's `count_at_least` gate has a baseline.
